INFLUENZA (12): USA, SWINE ORIGIN H3N2V, H1N2V
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 1 Nov 2021
Source: Fox [edited]
https://fox17.com/news/local/two-children-infected-with-flu-variant-normally-found-in-pigs-cdc-reports-illness-symptoms-flu-h1n1-winter-vaccines-health-doctors


The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) reports 2 new variants of the influenza (flu) virus normally found in pigs have now infected 2 children. CDC states variant virus flu infections are rare and usually take place from exposure to pigs with only a small number of infections unable to be traced to the animals. One of the new human infections took place where a person did have contact with pigs before illness, but in the other case there was no known pig exposure, meaning it could have been spread from human-to-human contact.

It is not believed the 2 cases spread the virus to any other humans. The new variants are part of the H3N2 and H1N1 groups. Neither child was hospitalized, and both have recovered [according to] CDC.

CDC says pigs can spread influenza viruses back and forth from the animals to humans and humans to animals through droplets, leading to new variants. The agency adds that those in close contact with pigs at home, work, or at fairs should take precautions to avoid human infection.

[byline: Adrian Mojica]

